title: Art of the Amur - Ancient Art of the Russian Far East (Art Ebook
description:
Pdf / English / 1981 / 158 pages / 31 MB

Recent archaeological finds near the Amur River have uncovered a very ancient culture that relates directly to the present-day peoples living in the same general area of Siberia.... There can hardly be another place in the world where an ancient art is so closely interwoven with contemporary life. Most of the archaeological and ethnographic objects shown in this book belong to two periods -- the Neolithic and the nineteenth and twentieth centuries.
